events.data: Hello I am really interested in this product
That's great. I'm interested in selling it to you.
How old is it?
The iphone 5 was first released in 2012, but I guess I don't remember when I bought it? It's almost like I would have remembered if I had thought to write it down in the product description. Oh well.
Thank you for the information. However, the price is too high for me. can we work on it?
Yes, I suppose we can negotiate. Let's negotiate, that's what I always say.
I can pay about $82 for it
Well, that's a pretty attractive offer. Now we just need to decide where to do the deal. Would you like to meet up in a Tmobile store or would you rather meet up at a gas station?
Gas station works really well for me. Thanks for the options. When can we do that?

Well, I always think it's best to wait until it's really dark and spooky to meet up at a gas station, maybe we can meet up at midnight, exchange the phone and just see where the night takes us from there. Maybe get some slurpees from the gas station?
Okay I think we're done with the deal and will meet up tomorrow then! Thanks
Great, looking forward to meeting you in a gas station.

events.data: This house looks perfect! Is there a basement?
unfortunately there is not a basement.
well is there anyway you could allow me to bring my cat along? I know you said no pets but I don't want to get rid of him

once again.  I am sorry, but i can't allow pets at this location. even the best pets do have occasional "accidents" and with this carpet can be very difficult to clean.  i certainly hope this isn't a deal breaker to you, but i understand if it is.
If you could lower the price to 2000 I would still take it.
what would you say to 2100 with a deposit of 1500, additionally, how is your credit?
I have decent credit but I just broke up with my boyfriend and all I can afford right now is to pay a little over 2000. I really need a place to live.
I understand, if you don't mind me asking, what is your current source of income?
I am a school teacher.

thank you for letting me know.  I appreciate the work you do.  you have been very pleasent during this process.  i'm willing to go down to 2000 in this situation.  assuming that you pass the credit check, which i'm sure that you will, we can get the lease agreement sorted out in about a week or so.
Thank you so much you won't regret this!
alright.  it sounds like 2000 is a deal.  thank you for your time.

events.data: Hello I am interested in buying.
Great!  I am listing this at 2250
I'm going to be honest with you, I am very very limited by my budget... I hope we can negotiate a fair price...
I understand.  However, this apartment has a lot of amenities that you may like.  It's clean, large, and close to the bay.  In fact, you can see the bay from the apartment
That sounds great. That countertop looks very outdated. I am stuck at 1350 but if the countertop was updated I could probably go much higher...
Well, we are not finished updating just yet.We still have to do the kitchen.  It's available on July 1st so we still have some time to replace it.  What's the highest you think you could go?
I think 1750 would be fair with a new countertop.

I really couldn't let it go for less than the 2250 asking price.  I am remodeling more than just the counter.  New carpet, new appliances, freshly painted and I put in an energy efficient HVAC so your utility bills will be lower.
That all sounds great but like I said I am limited by a very very low budget. I can forego the new countertop though if it means a fairer price.
How would you feel if I waived the first month's rent, but you have to agree to a 12 month lease?
I can't go any higher than 1750 and I didn't think you were coming back so I submitted it as my final offer.
I think with this location and the remodel's I'm putting in to it, I can't go 500 lower, so I'll have to reject your offer. Thank you for your interest, though.
Thanks for considering it. Have a good night.

events.data: Hello, I'd like to rent this apartment but I don't think the price is worth it especially since I cannot have my dog
While I cannot change the pets policy, I am willing to negotiate the price.
Is it possible to go as low as 1000/mo?
I am sorry, but that is too low. The apartment have modern furnishings, after all. I can do 1750/mo.
That's quite a bit over the list price, does this include any utilities?
It has shared and coined laundry machines. Air conditioning. Redone kitchen counter tops in 2014. Utilities, such as gas, internet, electric, must be covered by you.
What's the justification for renting at above the list price then? I currently rent a similar apartment down the street for $1250/mo and that includes a washer/dryer in the unit.
The location of the apartment is a factor. Also, the landlord pays for water, garbage, sewage, and HOA fees. So I feel you still are getting a good deal. But I can go down to 1600/mo.

I have a great deal of experience with landscaping, is it possible to negotiate a deal where I maintain the property for a deduction in the monthly rent? I can assure you my work is excellent and I can refer you to previous clients
I am sorry, but I cannot accept that offer. 1600/mo is my final offer.
I will accept 1600/mo then

Description: Come home to The Henley located in Suisun City, CA. The Henley is a short distance from Fairfield, Napa, Vacaville, Sacramento, San Francisco, and the greater Bay Area via Hwy 12 or I-80. Shopping will be a breeze with the Vacaville Outlets, Solano Mall and Westfield Mall close by. Want to get away? Driving will be quick to a number of fantastic destinations such as the Napa Valley Wine District, San Francisco Fisherman's Wharf, Suisun City Wildlife Center or Suisun City Marina. Local schools include Suisun Elementary, Crystal Middle School, Armijo High School, Solano Community College, National University-Fairfield and the University of Phoenix-Fairfield. Our spacious one and two bedroom apartment homes have been carefully designed with your friends and family in mind. Our recently renovated interiors feature refrigerators, dishwashers, and stoves with brushed nickel hardware, light fixture accents and two tone painted walls. events.data: hello
hello, I'm interested in your ap.

Well, what condition is it in?
It is like new and just a few months old.
Well, do you happen to know how easy it is to flash ddwrt to the device?
I have no idea.  Sorry.

Ok, $40 it is and you pick it up.

Description: Come home to The Henley located in Suisun City, CA. The Henley is a short distance from Fairfield, Napa, Vacaville, Sacramento, San Francisco, and the greater Bay Area via Hwy 12 or I-80. Shopping will be a breeze with the Vacaville Outlets, Solano Mall and Westfield Mall close by. Want to get away? Driving will be quick to a number of fantastic destinations such as the Napa Valley Wine District, San Francisco Fisherman's Wharf, Suisun City Wildlife Center or Suisun City Marina. Local schools include Suisun Elementary, Crystal Middle School, Armijo High School, Solano Community College, National University-Fairfield and the University of Phoenix-Fairfield. Our spacious one and two bedroom apartment homes have been carefully designed with your friends and family in mind. Our recently renovated interiors feature refrigerators, dishwashers, and stoves with brushed nickel hardware, light fixture accents and two tone painted walls. Catch some sun at the pool or enjoy our fully equipped fitness center that includes cardio, strength, and resistance equipment. The Henley is a pet friendly community, welcoming both cats and dogs.

Description: This is a vintage Peugeot 10-speed lugged road bike. It's a smaller bike, should be good for anyone 5'3'' and up.

This bike is NOT currently rideable. I'm selling it as is-- would be a great project bike or could be stripped down to the frame and built up. The tires/seat are worn and need replacement. The front derailleur is totally destroyed, and there are probably several other parts that need to be replaced. Some of the parts can definitely be salvaged though.
The bike has been sitting in a garage for years, so while it needs a lot of work, the frame itself is almost perfect. Hardly any scratches and a beautiful deep red color.

Description: I have NEW original, hard to find, Federal Pacific Electric ( FPE), also known as STAB-LOK,  later also made by American Circuit Breaker and Challenger.  These are NEW, original manufacturer, (OEM), breakers, not after market or refurbished (used and cleaned).  I also have brand new original FPE sub panels and service panels of different types.  I have more breakers of other sizes as well.  I bought this equipment many years ago, before I retired and when Federal Pacific was Federal Pacific Electric and produced high grade equipment.  FPE breakers later got a bad rap when after market breakers came in to the market.

Originally, Federal Pacific Electric ( FPE) was the only residential switching manufacturer using only copper, not aluminum, in their breakers and panels. This fact can be very important when installed near salt water, livestock or excessive moisture areas that can destroy aluminum.

Description: Open House: Sunday 12pm-2pm

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. This apartment gets plenty of sunlight all day, has lots of ample closet space, a separate living room, bathroom with claw-foot tub and hardwood floors.

The manor is located on the edge of the Gold Coast, just across the road from the Tree-and-Victorian-lined streets which make this beautiful residential enclave so famous. It is also located 1 block away from Franklin Park, a 15-20 minute walk to Park Street shops, restaurants and bars, and around the corner from buses ahead towards BART and throughout the Island.

item.Title: Fender Champion Amplifier

Description: I'm selling a Fender Champion 30 solid state practice amp.

It has two channels, one for clean and one for overdrive. The clean channel has a single volume control where the drive channel has separate gain and volume controls. Each channel shares a single 3 band EQ containing bass, middle and treble controls. There is also auxiliary, onboard reverb and a dual button footswitch available as well. It has a single speaker and puts out 30 watts of power overall.

Description: I have NEW original, hard to find, Federal Pacific Electric ( FPE), also known as STAB-LOK,  later also made by American Circuit Breaker and Challenger.  These are NEW, original manufacturer, (OEM), breakers, not after market or refurbished (used and cleaned).  I also have brand new original FPE sub panels and service panels of different types.  I have more breakers of other sizes as well.  I bought this equipment many years ago, before I retired and when Federal Pacific was Federal Pacific Electric and produced high grade equipment.  FPE breakers later got a bad rap when after market breakers came in to the market.

Originally, Federal Pacific Electric ( FPE) was the only residential switching manufacturer using only copper, not aluminum, in their breakers and panels. This fact can be very important when installed near salt water, livestock or excessive moisture areas that can destroy aluminum.

events.data: Hi! I hear you're interested in the Santa Clara apartment

No, you'll be responsible for furnishing it yourself.
Hmm that may be a problem with all of those steps we need to climb. The bed, the grand piano, the grandfather clock...
No worries! It's a first-floor apartment
Why was the unit extensively remodeled after only 2 years? Was there some sort of damage?

Not particularly. We like to replace all carpets after tenants who have pets -- even if there is not extensive damage, we find new tenants enjoy the brand-new features. If you think you might be interested in a tour, we can set something up?

Description: Gently Aligns the Spine
Safely Releases Pressure and Tension
Relieves Back Pain

Back2Life's Continuous Passive Motion releases the pressure to relieve the pain, increasing flexibility in your muscles and repositioning the vertebrae into correct anatomical alignment for long-term relief. Doctors and physical therapists often use Continuous Passive Motion to help patients suffering from conditions like sciatica, herniated discs, and back spasms. This method is designed to give you results gradually, safely, and easily.

Just two 12-minute sessions per day repeated over the course of a few days, weeks, or months - depending on your individual makeup and the severity of your condition - will have a cumulative impact on the health of your back and your overall quality of life.

events.data: Hi, I'm messaging you regarding the apartments for rent.
Hello, yes, do you have good credit? We are offering a discount to those with good credit?
Yea, credit's not a problem. I've got a 740+ FICO score. But let me ask you something. How big are the units?

They are approximately 565 sq. ft. Very reasonable for the area, very reasonable indeed. We are fairly close to the hills too, so they are much larger than you would find closer towards the water. Let me ask before I give you an offer, we are also adding a discount for those who have Equal Housing Opportunity vouchers. Do you have a voucher?

Are you kidding me? Over $2000 a month for a box that's less than 600 sq ft? And in Fremont? This isn't exactly downtown San Francisco we're talking about. For a unit that small I can't really do more than $1300 a month. I mean does the place come with maid service and free breakfast in the mornings?

Excellent, excellent. So no voucher. No I am not kidding you gentle person. I understand it is not San Francisco, but this is SF style and an excellent move towards the city. We only have the finest residents. We do a full background check, security. Everything an upscale person as yourself would want. We will give you a 10% discount because of your FICO score. Plus you get $500 when you move in! Don't forget about that!!
It's not worth the $2130, even with a one time discount of $500 dollars. You're going to have to give me a much better price than that.

events.data: Hey, is this car still available?
Yes, it is!
Was this serviced at BMW and do you have the service records?
I have all the service records and they are all up to date.
Perfect!  I do have to admit, I am a little concerned by the additional work though.  While it's appealing, I'm concerned about how it might affect the reliability.
I can guarantee that I have driven this car for about a year now and haven't had a single issue with it- the car runs perfectly and I have not had to conduct any repairs.
Ok, that's good.  I feel that 45,000 is a bit high though.  Of course, I do understand that it is a 2016 and has industry standard mileage.  Would you consider coming down on the price some?
The lowest I'm willing to drop it is 42,500. I've done some serious work to this car.
Fair, but I go get a 2017 from a dealer for a little more than you're asking.  If I pick up the car and handle all of the paperwork would you consider 38000?
38,000 just seems too low to me. I could do 41000 as long as you pay in cash, as well as picking up the car and taking care of all the paperwork yourself
I can do 40,000 cash, pick up and paperwork, but I'd expect the remainder of BMW's factory warranty to be transferred too.  Can we call that a deal?
Sounds good to me!
Perfect, thanks!

item.Title: Crestline tandem bike

Description: The first miles of tandem riding may be difficult, as the tandem seems to swerve around the road.  One experienced rider and one less experienced rider will take  about 100 miles. Captains may take 50 miles to get used to handling the big bike even without a stoker. Captaining a tandem is very much like riding a loaded touring bike, except the luggage pedals.

Try to be steady and predictable. Tandems don't handle like singles; you can't make sudden last second changes in direction or speed.  Stokers can make the problem much worse (without realizing it) by leaning  or attempting to steer. Stokers often lean slightly in an attempt to see around the captain. The stoker should be very quiet (little body movement) on the bike when you first start out until handling is in control and always quiet going downhill. . Stokers need to realize that their movements affect bike balance (steering)  Tandems are more stable at higher speeds than singles.

That's pretty big, but I can't afford that much. Could you go down if I have good credit?
We can offer one free month if you were to move in within the next 30 days. Would that help your budget at all?
I'm more interested in a lower rent. How about 1100?
Can we meet in the middle? $1600?
How about 1500?
Great!

15,000 and that is the highest I can go.

events.data: Hi there is the car still there?
Yes it is
How old is it?
the car is a 2016
and how is the ride?
This car is just great.   I just love it.  Is has all power and leather seats.
did it go any mechanical service recently?
It has been looked over and is in good condition. YOu could test drive it and take it to your mechanic for verification if you would like.
okay sounds good to me. WHat about the price? Its way too high for me. Is there room for negotiation here?
I could come down to 15000 and throw in a 2 year warranty on the power train.  I can also give you the first 3 oil changes for free.
Wow my budget is somewhere around $10990
I just can't do that low, i'm sorry.  I tell you what I'll do 14500 for you. it is a good price for a car 1 year old with only 1523 miles.
Does 12000$ sound reasonable? Please I am really on a tight budget?
I'm sorry but that's 5000 under the blue book value of this car.   My final offer is 14000 that's the best I can do.  I need to pay off the car myself.
Okay would you be willing to accept installments? I mean I can pay monthly?
Yes that would be just fine.
Okay then we've got it covered! Thanks
That's great glad we could make this deal work.

Description: The details on this midcentury piece combine to turn an ordinary nightstand into something more understated. The subtle taper of the legs draw inspiration from 60's Danish design and the drawer pull is framed with an elegant wooden feature. Coasters won't be needed in the company of this piece as the top has a layer of formica protecting it. Bears the usual dings and scratches near the bottom of the legs that a well-loved side table would. Features the Lane logo on the botton and inside of the drawer.
This vintage mid-century modern walnut piece can be use as a coffee table / side table / nightstand and will bring sophisticated style to any space.  Features a lower shelf for additional storage.
